criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Individuals with stage II and III between the Hoehn and Yahr classification;

          -  minimum score of 28 on the Mini Mental Examination for Parkinson.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  individuals with rheumatologic or orthopedic diseases or deformities / abnormalities
             in the spine that compromise the respiratory mechanics;

          -  respiratory comorbidities;

          -  history of smoking;

          -  history of thoracic or abdominal surgery;

          -  clinical instability characterized by infections and / or hemodynamic defined as
             greater than 150 bpm heart rate or systolic blood pressure less than 90 mmHg;

          -  Not present exchange of the drug in the last 30 days.
